<!--
File: game.fxml
Purpose: FXML layout definition for the Word Definition Game user interface

This file defines the visual layout and structure of the game using JavaFX FXML markup.
It creates an AnchorPane-based layout with labels for displaying the word and definitions,
panes representing different parts of speech as drop zones, buttons for navigation, and
a score display. The controller attribute links this view to the Controller class.

Key UI Components:
- root (AnchorPane): Main container with 600x565 dimensions
- wordLabel: Large bold label displaying the current word (36pt font)
- scoreLabel: Displays current score in 24pt font
- d1, d2, d3: Three gray labels (441x40px) showing definitions that can be dragged
- nounPane, verbPane, adjectivePane, adverbPane, prepositionPane, conjunctionPane: Drop zones (40x40px) for matching parts of speech
- otherPane: Skip/other category drop zone (50x50px)
- NextWord Button: Triggers loading of the next word
- Static labels: Show part-of-speech category names above drop zones
- Image: Placeholder ImageView (200x84px) for potential word illustrations

Layout coordinates are specified using layoutX/layoutY for precise positioning.
The controller is bound to ca.additional.practice.javafx.worddefinitionsgame.Controller.
-->
